"text": "Bauxite deposits are often extracted using strip mining techniques that remove large surface areas.",
"source": "health_book_draft:chapter_three_section_1"
},
{
"text": "Strip mining can alter local ecosystems even when land reclamation efforts are undertaken.",
"source": "health_book_draft:chapter_three_section_1"
}
]
},
{
"type": "item",
"canonical_name": "Red mud",
"aliases": [],
"claims": [
{
"text": "Red mud is a residual byproduct of the Bayer Process containing caustic and metallic elements.",
