"text": "Vitamin C is described as a nutrient that can interact with aluminum in ways that either promote excretion or enhance cellular absorption depending on timing and individual health.",
"source": "health_book_draft:chunk_37"
},
{
"text": "Staggering vitamin C intake away from aluminum-rich foods or medications is presented as a strategy to reduce aluminum absorption.",
